How do you do something like this in the web view tag?

```
webContents.on('will-navigate', function(event, url) {
    if (isExternal(url)) {
        event.preventDefault();
        openInExternalPage(url);
    }
});
```

(given that the url can be changed by clicking a link or setting window.location)

@yyjhao Actually, I spoke too soon. Here's a way you could (almost) do that:

Injection script:

``` javascript
  window.onbeforeunload = function() {
      ipc.sendToHost('webview:beforenavigate', window.location.href);
  }
```

Webview:

``` javascript
    webview.addEventListener('ipc-message', function(e) {
      } if(e.channel == "webview:beforenavigate") {
        webview.stop();
        openInExternalPage(e.args[0]); // Probably isn't the new URL, Not sure how to do that part yet.
      }
    });
```

I'm not sure if there's a way to get the URL though, none of the methods I've tried have worked.

