Supporting `event.preventDefault()` on `will-navigate` from the `<webview>` element API is probably not feasible. `will-navigate` is a main process event that is fired on the `webContents` object. To enable it there would need to be a mechanism to do IPC events synchronously from the main process to a render process so that cancel could be properly handled.

Is there something preventing this from being managed by applications in the main process?

For the use case of opening links externally, would the following not work?

```js
app.on('web-contents-created', (event, contents) => {
  if (contents.getType() == 'webview') {
    contents.on('will-navigate', (event, url) => {
      event.preventDefault()
      shell.openExternal(url)
    })
  }
})
```

